# Booking.com Hotel Reviews Analysis
This repository contains data and analysis for guest reviews and ratings of hotels across Europe scraped from popular hotel reservation website Booking.com. The dataset is stored in the file BookingDotCom_HotelReviews.xlsx. The text data has been preprocessed by removing unicode and punctuation and transforming to lower case.

## Data Description
Data Context:
This dataset contains 515,000 customer reviews and scoring of 1493 luxury hotels across Europe scraped from popular hotel reservation website Booking.com. 
All data is publicly available, but originally owned byÂ Booking.com. 
The text data was cleaned by removing unicode and punctuation and by transforming text into lower case. No other preprocessing was performed.

Data Description:
Hotel_Name: Name of hotel
Hotel_Address: Address of hotel, including city and country
Review_Count: Total number of valid reviews for this hotel
Non_Review_Scoring_Count: Count of guests who  scored the hotel on service but did not leave a review. This number indicates the number of valid scores without review 
Average_Hotel_Score: Average Score of the hotel, calculated based on the latest comment in the last year.
Review_Date: Date when reviewer posted his/her review.
Reviewer_Nationality: Nationality of Reviewer
Positive_Review: Positive Review the reviewer gave to the hotel. 'No Positive' means that reviewer did not leave a positive review.
Negative_Review: Negative Review the reviewer gave to the hotel. 'No Negative' means that reviewer did not leave a negative review.
Total_Reviewer_Review: Number of reviews the reviewers has given in the past
Reviewer_Score: Score the reviewer has given to the hotel, based on his/her experience
Tags: Tags reviewer gave the hotel.

## Analysis
Top Features in Reviews
Positive Reviews:
Identify the top five hotel features that customers mention most positively.
Negative Reviews:
Identify the top five features that customers mention most negatively.
Preferences based on Traveler Type
Identify the top five features preferred by customers based on the following traveler types:

Solo Travelers
Groups
Business Travelers
Leisure Travelers
Couples
Families with Young Children

## Top Features by Country
Identify the top five features liked most and complained about most by customers in the following countries:

United Kingdom
France
Italy
Spain

## Dashboard Plots
### Top Five Hotels Overall: 
Display hotels with consistently high ratings.
### Bottom Five Hotels Overall: 
Display hotels with consistently low ratings.
### Five Most Improved Hotels: 
Display hotels with the highest improvement in average ratings from 2015 to 2017, showing their average ratings for each of the three years.
